# Shell scripts and Linux config/units MUST stay LF: a CRLF "#!/usr/bin/env bash"
# becomes "bad interpreter: /usr/bin/env bash^M" on Debian/Proxmox, and CRLF can
# trip systemd/Caddy/mongod configs. Pin them so a Windows checkout can't flip
# them to CRLF (overrides core.autocrlf).
*.sh        text eol=lf
*.bash      text eol=lf
*.service   text eol=lf
*.timer     text eol=lf
*.conf      text eol=lf
Caddyfile   text eol=lf
